<br>
I have all three staves (gnarled, gabstick and blue crystal), but I do not have the note to aranthir anymore.<br>
<br>
Is there a way to finish the epic without doing the broken golem quest once again ?<br>
<br>
By waiting for Aranthir from a wizard about to finish his epic as well, for instance (if he doesn't depop right after giving the bag) ?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mctardiss>McTardiss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/03 6:38:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sorry to say....</span><hr size=1> Sadly, he does depop right when you turn in the staffs and get the bag, so you can't just do it when another wizard does their turn-in.  And versions of Arantir spawned using Ro's Breath and such are different versions of Arantir.<br>
<br>
The *only* way to do the staff turn-in is to use the Note TO Arantir.  Yes, you have to redo the Fear Golem part if you no longer have the note.<br>
<br>
Not the news you wanted to hear, I'm sure.  GL getting the Golem again - at least he's not broken anymore, like he was a couple months ago.<br>
<br>
Ophiuchi<br>
Fallen Eagles<br>
