<br>
Every method of spawning Arantir gets a DIFFERENT version of Arantir.  Hand in the &quot;Note To Arantir&quot; to get the one ready to recieve the staffs.  Hand in the potion, and you get a version who won't know what to do with the staffs, and will either eat them or just return them.  Either way, you're out 1kpp at least.<br>
<br>
-Oph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zerlatikflaimweaver>Zerlatik Flaimweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/03 7:20:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Because....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Either way, you're out 1kpp at least.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not quite, all he really needs to do is go back to Kandin and ask for a new gear.  You then redo the BG raid, (Yes, your life now sucks, but that's what happens when you eat the note), and Kandin gives you a new reward for the stuff.  Since you already have Gabstik's staff, you'll get a duplicate lore item message, but you will get the note also.  If you want to make absolutely certain, you can delete the old Gabstik, (THE HORROR!), and recieve a new one as well as a new note.<br>
<br>
Not what you wanted to hear, I'm sure, but it saves you 1kpp you can now blow on tradeskills or something else.<br>
